# fast-secrets — example requests (PyCharm / VS Code REST client)

### List every generator + its options (drives the UI)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/generators
Accept: application/json

### Quick UUID (v4) — convenient GET form
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/generate/uuid
Accept: application/json

### Five time-sortable UUID v7s
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/generate/uuid?version=7&count=5
Accept: application/json

### Password, plain text (one per line — great for scripts)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/generate/password?length=24&symbols=true&count=3&format=text
Accept: text/plain

### Hex token (32 bytes)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/generate/hex?nbytes=32
Accept: application/json

### API key with a custom prefix (POST form for rich options)
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{ "type": "apikey", "options": { "prefix": "sk_live", "nbytes": 32 }, "count": 2 }

### Generate several at once
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/generate/batch
Content-Type: application/json

[
  { "type": "uuid", "count": 2 },
  { "type": "ulid", "count": 2 },
  { "type": "passphrase", "options": { "words": 5 } }
]

### One of everything (defaults)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/all
Accept: application/json

### SHA-256 of some input
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/generate/hash?text=hello&algorithm=sha256
Accept: application/json

###
